node.text: Following on from my support of @mindcharity through the @leytonorientfc partnership I’m proud to be supporting #MentalHealthMinute with @heads_together and @radiocentre_uk. Whoever you are, and whatever you’re going through, it’s important that you remember you’re not alone. #MentalHealthAwarenessWeek

node.text:
What does Greatness mean to you? #DisplayGreatness

For me, it's about leading from the front, setting up teammates and scoring goals.

I'm giving away some great prizes with @tclmobile_uk for our favourite comments. Prizes are a TCL Football shirt signed by me, the brand new TCL 20 Pro 5G or a TCL TAB 10 MAX tablet. To enter:

1) Comment below, or post a story or a grid post, telling us what Greatness means to you.
2) Tag and follow @TCLMobile_UK.
3) Use #DisplayYourGreatness.

Competition closes 29 July, winners contacted on 30 July. UK residents only. Good luck! T&Cs on TCL website.

node.text: A week to reflect on a summer I’ll never forget. Makes me even hungrier for World Cup success in 2022. Thanks for all the amazing support. Time for a break. ☀️

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Harry Kane on July 12, 2021 tagging @marcusrashford, @sanchooo10, @bukayosaka87, and @england. May be an image of 6 people.

node.text: Three lads who were brilliant all summer and who had the courage to step up and take a penalty when the stakes were high. They deserve our support and backing not the vile racist abuse they’ve had since last night. If you’re abusing anyone on social media you’re not an England fan and we don’t want you.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Harry Kane on July 12, 2021 tagging @england. May be an image of stadium.

node.text: Last night hurts. It’ll hurt for a long time. But we’ve come so far and broken down so many barriers that this is not the end. We win together, lose together and will regroup together for the World Cup. Thanks for all your support this summer.
